    "text": "Glenville, NY (WRGB) â€” The driver of the truck carrying compressed natural gas that struck the Maple Avenue railroad bridge in Glenville, then exploded into flames on Dec. 21, is facing charges. [ORIGINAL REPORT: Maple Avenue remains closed after truck strikes bridge and explodes](https://cbs6albany.com/news/local/propane-truck-strikes-maple-avenue-railroad-bridge-explodes-town-supervisor) Chris Koetzle, Supervisor, Town of Glenville, confirmed Thursday that the town is filing charges against Sylvester Basil Jr. under new town code put in place in response to repeated bridge strikes. Though still recovering Basil Jr. is charged with failure to obey a bridge sign. [NEIGHBORS REACT: 'By far the worst': Bridge strike explosion along Glenville's Maple Ave shakes neighbors homes](https://cbs6albany.com/news/local/by-far-the-worst-bridge-strike-turned-explosion-along-glenvilles-maple-ave#) According to Police Chief Stephen Janik, it is a simple criminal summons for a town code violation. He may decide to appear or not, but if he does not appear, the court may issue a warrant.",
